# E2E testing (Playwright)

Use **Playwright directly** for real-browser coverage. Each package owns its scenarios under `packages/<name>/e2e/`. Do **not** put E2E specs in `packages/<name>/test/` and do **not** use Vitest browser mode.

Full reference: `docs/e2e-testing.md`. Reference implementation: `packages/theme/e2e/`.

## When to write E2E

| Write E2E when… | Keep in happy-dom when… |
|-----------------|-------------------------|
| Focus trap, capture, restore | State machine, events, cleanup |
| Real keyboard navigation (Tab, Escape, arrows) | Store/magic registration |
| Portals, teleport, nested overlays | ARIA attribute literals without focus |
| Scroll locking, layout measurement | Options normalization, errors |
| Browser APIs (`matchMedia`, permissions, observers) | Controller logic without DOM |

Every package does **not** need E2E on day one. Add a project when happy-dom cannot model the behavior faithfully.

## Package layout

```text
packages/<name>/
  playwright.config.ts
  e2e/
    fixture/
      index.html    # minimal Alpine markup
      main.ts       # registers the plugin under test
    <feature>.spec.ts
```

Shared repo infrastructure (do not duplicate per package):

- `e2e/playwright.base.ts` — `definePackagePlaywrightConfig()`
- `e2e/fixtures.ts` — `test`, `expect`, `waitForAlpineFixture()`
- `e2e/server/start-fixture-server.mjs` — bundles fixture and serves `/`, `/app.js`, `/__health`

## Scaffold checklist

1. Create `packages/<name>/e2e/fixture/index.html` with `data-e2e-ready="true"` on the bootstrapped root.
2. Create `packages/<name>/e2e/fixture/main.ts` — import Alpine + plugin, call `Alpine.plugin(...)`, then `Alpine.start()`.
3. Create `packages/<name>/playwright.config.ts`:

```typescript
import path from "node:path";
import { fileURLToPath } from "node:url";
import { definePackagePlaywrightConfig } from "../../e2e/playwright.base.js";

const packageDir = path.dirname(fileURLToPath(import.meta.url));

export default definePackagePlaywrightConfig({
  packageName: "<name>",
  packageDir,
});
```

4. Add to `packages/<name>/package.json`:

```json
"test:e2e": "playwright test --config playwright.config.ts",
"test:e2e:report": "playwright show-report e2e/playwright-report"
```

5. Add specs under `packages/<name>/e2e/*.spec.ts`.

## Fixture patterns by plugin type

### Store plugin

`main.ts` — register the store plugin with deterministic options:

```typescript
import myPlugin from "@ailuracode/alpine-my";
import Alpine from "alpinejs";

Alpine.plugin(myPlugin({ /* minimal options for the scenario */ }));
Alpine.start();
```

`index.html` — exercise `$store.<name>` and user actions:

```html
<main data-e2e-ready="true" x-data x-init>
  <button type="button" @click="$store.my.action()">Run action</button>
  <output x-text="$store.my.value"></output>
</main>
<script type="module" src="/app.js"></script>
```

### Magic-only plugin

Register the magic in `main.ts`. Bind magics in markup with `x-text` / `@click` on the magic return value (for object magics, expose methods on the returned object).

### Directive plugin

Put the directive on a host element in `index.html`. Keep markup minimal but include the attributes consumers would use (`x-child`, etc.).

### Multiple workspace dependencies

Import from `@ailuracode/alpine-*` package names in `main.ts`. The fixture server resolves workspace aliases from root `tsconfig.json` — do not hardcode relative paths to other packages' `src/`.

## Writing specs

Always import from the shared fixtures module:

```typescript
import { expect, test, waitForAlpineFixture } from "../../../e2e/fixtures.js";

test.describe("@ailuracode/alpine-<name>", () => {
  test("describes user-visible behavior", async ({ page }) => {
    await page.goto("/");
    await waitForAlpineFixture(page);

    await expect(page.getByRole("button", { name: "Run action" })).toBeEnabled();
    await page.getByRole("button", { name: "Run action" }).click();
    await expect(page.getByRole("status")).toHaveText("expected");
  });
});
```

Rules:

- `describe("@ailuracode/alpine-<name>", …)` — match package scope.
- One behavior per `test()`; prefer two focused specs over one long flow.
- Call `waitForAlpineFixture(page)` once after `page.goto("/")` — only for Alpine boot, not for every assertion.
- Uncaught page errors fail the test automatically (configured in `e2e/fixtures.ts`).

## Selectors and accessibility

| Priority | Use |
|----------|-----|
| 1 | `page.getByRole("button", { name: "…" })` |
| 2 | `page.getByRole("dialog")`, `getByLabel`, `getByText` |
| 3 | `data-testid` when roles are insufficient |
| Avoid | CSS classes, XPath, `nth-child`, `#id` unless stable and documented |

Assert accessibility in E2E with role visibility, enabled/disabled, and focus where relevant. Detailed ARIA contracts may stay in happy-dom tests.

## Waiting policy

- Rely on Playwright auto-waiting: `expect(locator)`, `click()`, `fill()`.
- **Forbidden**: `page.waitForTimeout()`.
- **Forbidden**: manual `sleep` helpers.
- Use `expect(…).toBeVisible()` / `toHaveText()` / `toHaveAttribute()` — they retry until timeout.

## Anti-flake rules

- Fixtures must be **deterministic** — fixed options, no random IDs, no network calls unless the scenario requires them (then stub in the spec).
- Keep one plugin (plus required peers) per fixture page.
- Do not share mutable `localStorage` state across specs — the fixture server serves a fresh page; reset in `main.ts` options if needed.
- Do not start extra servers or processes from specs — Playwright `webServer` owns the fixture server lifecycle.
- Headless CSS in fixtures is allowed only for layout needed by the scenario; stay headless-policy compliant (no Tailwind/framework classes in `packages/**` except devtools exempt paths).

## Commands

```bash
pnpm run playwright:install
pnpm --filter @ailuracode/alpine-<name> test:e2e
pnpm run test:e2e
pnpm run test:e2e:affected
PWDEBUG=1 pnpm --filter @ailuracode/alpine-<name> test:e2e   # debug
```

## Common mistakes

| Mistake | Fix |
|---------|-----|
| E2E spec in `packages/<name>/test/` | Move to `packages/<name>/e2e/*.spec.ts` |
| Vitest `describe` / `it` in E2E | Use Playwright `test` / `test.describe` from `e2e/fixtures.js` |
| Import `@playwright/test` directly | Import `test`, `expect` from `../../../e2e/fixtures.js` |
| `domStrategy` in theme options | Use `strategy` (see `CreateThemeOptions`) |
| Reassign `readonly` store fields in plugin code | Sync in place with `Object.assign` on a mutable backing object |
| `page.waitForTimeout(500)` | Use `expect(locator).…` auto-wait |
| Centralized `e2e/packages/*` directory | Keep specs in the owning package |
| Skip `playwright.config.ts` | Every E2E package needs its own config calling `definePackagePlaywrightConfig` |
| Missing `data-e2e-ready` in fixture HTML | Add to bootstrapped root so `waitForAlpineFixture` can gate Alpine init |

Run `pnpm --filter @ailuracode/alpine-<name> test:e2e` before finishing E2E work.
